description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join an Award Winning multidisciplinary community team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The community elderly virtual ward Team, deliver care closer to home. Interacting with the Consultant Interface Geriatrician, therapist, nursing and social care team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will deliver seamless care across organisational boundaries reviewing patients in a community setting in order to improve the ability for patients to self-care; to enable patients to recover at home following illness/ preventing the need for patients to be admitted to hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Brief Description of the Role: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Summary of most important Experience/Skills/Qualifications required:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced health care worker, to work as part of a multidisciplinary team and provide skills, knowledge and expertise in the care and management of frail older patients in a community setting. You will support nursing and therapy staff to deliver both nursing care and support enablement programmes to patients in their own homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential qualifications;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maths and English GSCE grade c and above&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NVQ/ Diploma level 3 in health and social care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;IT IS ESSENTIAL TO HAVE A UK DRIVING LICENCE AND HAVE A CARE AVAILAVBLE FOR WORK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
